{
  "name": "cerebellar_circuit",
  "description": "Minimal cerebellum — error-correction motor learning. Real cerebellum: granule cells (input) → Purkinje cells (processing, inhibit output) → deep cerebellar nuclei (output). Climbing fibers carry error signal that pauses Purkinje firing. Our version: 2 RS mossy fibers receive input. 1 IB Purkinje-analog tonically fires and inhibits 2 RS deep nucleus outputs. Error input drives CH climbing fiber → FS basket cell burst → kills Purkinje. With Purkinje killed, deep nucleus is disinhibited and fires. STDP on mossy→deep_nucleus: mossy (pre) fired, then deep_nucleus (post) fires because disinhibited = LTP. Over many errors, mossy→deep_nucleus grows strong enough that deep nucleus fires even without error. The error has TAUGHT the direct pathway. LTS Golgi cell provides sustained input regulation. Implements: motor error correction, adaptive timing, supervised learning via error signals.",
  "nodes": [
    {"id": 0, "type": "RS", "x": 0.0, "z": 0.0},
    {"id": 1, "type": "RS", "x": 0.0, "z": 2.0},

    {"id": 2, "type": "IB", "x": 2.0, "z": 1.0},

    {"id": 3, "type": "CH", "x": 0.0, "z": 4.0, "params": {"a": 0.02, "c": -55.0, "d": 4.0}},
    {"id": 4, "type": "FS", "x": 2.0, "z": 3.0},

    {"id": 5, "type": "LTS", "x": 2.0, "z": -1.0},

    {"id": 6, "type": "RS", "x": 4.0, "z": 0.0},
    {"id": 7, "type": "RS", "x": 4.0, "z": 2.0}
  ],
  "paths": [
